(31,1,'2025-05-07 07:58:58','2025-05-07 07:58:58','<h2>🧠 Lesson 1: Your First C Program – Hello World</h2>\r\n<h3>🎯 Goal:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Write a simple program that prints <code>Hello, World!</code> to the screen.</li>\r\n 	<li>Learn the structure of a basic C program.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>📝 C Program Structure</h3>\r\n<pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;  // Preprocessor directive\r\n\r\nint main() {        // Main function: Entry point\r\n    printf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");  // Output to console\r\n    return 0;       // Exit code (0 = success)\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n<h3>🔍 Explanation</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Line</th>\r\n<th>Purpose</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</code></td>\r\n<td>Includes the standard input/output library to use <code>printf</code>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>int main()</code></td>\r\n<td>Main function – where the program starts executing.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>{ ... }</code></td>\r\n<td>Code block – contains the body of the function.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>printf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");</code></td>\r\n<td>Prints the string to the screen. <code>\\n</code> means new line.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>return 0;</code></td>\r\n<td>Returns 0 to signal successful execution.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>🧪 Try It Yourself</h3>\r\n<strong>1. Requirements:</strong>\r\nInstall a C compiler like <em>GCC</em> (Linux/macOS) or <em>MinGW</em> (Windows).\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Save this code in a file called <code>hello.c</code>:</strong>\r\n<pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\r\n\r\nint main() {\r\n    printf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");\r\n    return 0;\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n<strong>3. Compile it:</strong>\r\n<pre><code>gcc hello.c -o hello</code></pre>\r\n<strong>4. Run the program:</strong>\r\n<pre><code>./hello</code></pre>\r\nYou should see:\r\n<pre><code>Hello, World!</code></pre>\r\n<h3>💡 Exercises</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Modify the message</strong> – Change <code>\"Hello, World!\"</code> to something else.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Add another line</strong> – Print your name on a second line.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Remove the <code>\\n</code></strong> – What happens?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>📚 What\'s Next?</h3>\r\nIn the next lessons, you’ll learn:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>How to use variables</li>\r\n 	<li>How to take user input</li>\r\n 	<li>How to use if-statements and loops</li>\r\n</ul>','first program inc','','private','open','closed','','first-program-inc','','','2025-05-07 08:00:32','2025-05-07 08:00:32','',0,'http://0.0.0.0:8000/?post_type=lp_lesson&#038;p=31',0,'lp_lesson','',0),
(32,1,'2025-05-07 07:58:58','2025-05-07 07:58:58','&lt;h2&gt;🧠 Lesson 1: Your First C Program – Hello World&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;🎯 Goal:&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Write a simple program that prints &lt;code&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/code&gt; to the screen.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Learn the structure of a basic C program.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;📝 C Program Structure&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#include &amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt; // Preprocessor directive\r\n\r\nint main() { // Main function: Entry point\r\nprintf(\"Hello, World!\\n\"); // Output to console\r\nreturn 0; // Exit code (0 = success)\r\n}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;🔍 Explanation&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;table&gt;\r\n&lt;thead&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Line&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Purpose&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;/thead&gt;\r\n&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;#include &amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Includes the standard input/output library to use &lt;code&gt;printf&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;int main()&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Main function – where the program starts executing.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;{ ... }&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Code block – contains the body of the function.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;printf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Prints the string to the screen. &lt;code&gt;\\n&lt;/code&gt; means new line.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;return 0;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Returns 0 to signal successful execution.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;🧪 Try It Yourself&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Install a C compiler like &lt;em&gt;GCC&lt;/em&gt; (Linux/macOS) or &lt;em&gt;MinGW&lt;/em&gt; (Windows).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Save this code in a file called &lt;code&gt;hello.c&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#include &amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;\r\n\r\nint main() {\r\nprintf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");\r\nreturn 0;\r\n}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Compile it:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;gcc hello.c -o hello&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Run the program:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;./hello&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;You should see:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;💡 Exercises&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;ol&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modify the message&lt;/strong&gt; – Change &lt;code&gt;\"Hello, World!\"&lt;/code&gt; to something else.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Add another line&lt;/strong&gt; – Print your name on a second line.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remove the &lt;code&gt;\\n&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; – What happens?&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;📚 What\'s Next?&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the next lessons, you’ll learn:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;How to use variables&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;How to take user input&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;How to use if-statements and loops&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;','first program inc','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2025-05-07 07:58:58','2025-05-07 07:58:58','',31,'http://0.0.0.0:8000/?p=32',0,'revision','',0),
